main event: Two bright fireballs were observed revolving and seeming to form one large object over Bournemouth, England on October 19, 1945.
interesting points: The sighting involved two bright fireballs observed at a high elevation moving in an easterly direction at high speed., The observation lasted for approximately 15 seconds., The observer reported that no stars or aircraft were associated with the sighting., The conclusion indicated insufficient data to arrive at a definite conclusion., The sighting was part of Project 10073 under Project Blue Book.
witness description: The observer was at a high elevation, viewing the objects moving quickly across the sky.
